Citations
Date:  25/5/1850
Source:  Nelson Examiner and New Zealand Chronicle
Author:
Vol / Page:  50
Edition:
Quote:  At Taipo, at Tata, at Takaka, at Aurere, at all points, in fact, of this extensive district, coal is known to abound, and by cropping out, as it does in several seams, at West Wanganui, or on the other western side of the coast, there can be scarcely a doubt but that the whole of that part of the island is a vast coal-field.
