Vol / Page:  2
Edition:
Quote:  The extent of flat land is considerable, chiefly wooded, and these districts are opened up for a short distance by their respective rivers; limestone is to be obtained in any quantity; coal at the Taipo, and Tata, at the Motupipi, and the Takaka.
